      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DEMBE (4) comes here following a sixth behind Im No Trouble at Listed level five-and-a-half months ago over 1740m at Riverina Paceway. Ideally drawn and can return in winning form. HELLOVATIME (8) again drew a wide gate last start but did a good job, beaten 9 metres into second at Cranbourne over 1609m. Will enjoy a pretty soft run from this draw, with the sprint lane to play a big role. Won't find this any harder and he can feature in the finish. ROMAN SCRITTORE (6) got home by 2.5 metres over 1690m at this track last start at his first race start. Strips fitter and can go back-to-back without surprising. UNCLE TREV (3) is better than his last-start seventh over 1690m here. Worth another chance.",
